column5: I wouldn't be opposed to that lol.
Excellent fish! Well done. Love the dark green.
Beauti. Better than sex, I say. ?

Thanks everybody. It was quite the adrenaline rush. She took some hard runs too, my wife wasn't sure which side to take the net since it was back and forth.  I had another BIG one turn on a figure 8 today but just wouldn't open it's mouth. 3 follows and no takers, first time I've been skunked in 6 trips but I don't even care right now lol.   She showed you where she is, pick your time and she will bite,

Well I started out musky fishing in 2011. I didn't know what I was doing but this board helped me out a lot. Special shout of to Mike Rousseau, the day we got out fishing was a real learning experience. I was still stuck on that 44.5" musky as my personal best, though. I was catching fish, just nothing big. That changed yesterday.          My first 50" fish!
Nice fish!!!! Congrats.  I see you still have the same boat; I sure do miss that thing.  Dan.
She's been awful good to me Dan. Though she's not as pretty as she once was.
She's been awful good to me Dan. Though she's not as pretty as she once was.  All that means is that you're getting good use out of her.  Congrats again on the 50"er!!!  Dan.
Well done on the 50, some guys never reach that mark.  Real pretty fish !!
Congrats it's a great feeling
What a beautiful fish!!! Congratulations on the breaking the 50!!!
What a beast!  Your smile says it all. Congrats!
Way to go. Welcome to the club
Well done.  That is one gorgeous looking Musky.  Cheers,  Mark
Well done dood!  Beauty fish. Congrats.  You'll be on cloud 9 all summer thinking about it.
dunno whats bigger your smile or that fish!  well done...what lake were you fishing?
Wowza is all I can say, wowza.
Oh sweet.  Congrats.   I'm still holding on for my first 50" .  Always glad to hear when others hit it.
Nice man. Good start to the season! Should be a good one
Nice! I still havent got a 50!!  S.
Great fish, thanks for sharing!
Awesome dude!

Nice work! Congrats!!!  That area looks very familiar... I've spent a lot of hours out there and still haven't netted my 50. Well done!  I heard yesterday was a crazy day on the water everywhere. Something about that kind of early summer weather pattern that gets animals revved up I guess. Got that big girl to eat!
A nice fish for sure, congrats!
Nice deep/clean colour on that fish! Real beauty!  Congrats on 50! Now the hard part, eclipsing that beast!  Thanks for sharing!
An excellent fish by any standard!

Thanks everybody. It was quite the adrenaline rush. She took some hard runs too, my wife wasn't sure which side to take the net since it was back and forth.  I had another BIG one turn on a figure 8 today but just wouldn't open it's mouth. 3 follows and no takers, first time I've been skunked in 6 trips but I don't even care right now lol.
Thats a purdy fish.  Well done.
Well done!!!  That's a nice fish  Now that you raised the bar we will have to fish again to try and break it lol
